I"><p>If <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/epistemic-action-generalizes-cognitive-outsourcing">epistemic action is based on using the environment as a collaborator in cognitive tasks</a>, then the minimal control principle is a guideline for offloading as much <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/perceptual-load-modulates-distractibility">cognitive load</a> as possible onto the environment, and tweaking behaviors towards high <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/context-independent-strategies-are-like-good-chess-moves">context-dependence</a>.</p>
